            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Requires chemical treatment.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Calgon is a commercial name for Sodium ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Hexametaphosphate (Na6P6O18)</option><option id="B">Carbonate</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Used for water softening.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Hydrogen Peroxide (H2O2) is an important ____ used in pollution control.</text>
            <option id="A">Oxidizing / Reducing agent</option><option id="B">Fuel</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Eco-friendly oxidant.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Structure of H2O2 is ____.</text>
